process.name: Test Send Keys with Interval
process.narrative: Tests SendKeys and related actions after the Interval parameter is added, namely: * Global Send Keys * Global Send Key Events * Window Press Keys * Window Press Keys with Alt

stage.name: Start
stage.narrative: Reads the text from Notepad, checking that it either matches the Expected Text or contains the Expected SubText, depending on which is given (Expected Text takes priority, if both are present)

input.name: Expected Text
input.narrative: The expected text in Notepad

input.name: Expected SubText
input.narrative: The text expected to be found somewhere in the text in Notepad

input.name: Clear?
input.narrative: Clear the text after a successful test

input.name: Page Name
input.narrative: The name of the page which is running the test

input.name: Test
input.narrative: The name of the test

decision.expression: ([Expected Text] <> "" AND [Text] = [Expected Text]) OR ([Expected SubText] <> "" AND InStr([Text], [Expected SubText]) > 0)

exception.detail: "Test: " & [Page Name] & " / " & [Test] & " - Expected the text: '" & [Expected Text] & "'; Found: '" & [Text] & "'"
"Expected the subtext: '" & [Expected Text] & "'; No such subtext found in: '" & [Text] & "'"

stage.name: Note1
stage.narrative: Neither a full nor a subtext be. Well, *anything* contains an empty string, so we treat that as a success, odd test though it may be. The caller clearly knows something we don't.
